{
  "info": {
    "name": "URL Shortener",
    "description": "Endpoints for the URL shortener (Better Auth + organization multitenancy + shorten/redirect/analytics).\n\nCollection variables:\n- baseUrl: http://localhost:3000\n- sessionToken: auto-filled from the `set-auth-token` response header on Sign Up / Sign In\n- verificationToken: paste the `token` query param from the verification email link\n- jwtToken: auto-filled by Get JWT Token (optional, for stateless validation)\n- shortCode: auto-filled by Create Short URL\n- organizationId: auto-filled by Create Organization / Get Session (the active tenant)\n- orgSlug: slug used when creating an organization\n- invitationId: auto-filled by Invite Member\n- memberId: auto-filled by List Members\n\nMULTITENANCY\nThe URL routes are tenant-scoped via the Better Auth organization plugin. On sign-up every user automatically gets a personal organization (as owner), and each new session is pinned to the user's first organization as the active tenant. All /api/urls operations act within the active organization. Switch tenants with `Organization > Set Active Organization`.\n\nFlow (production): Sign Up -> check email -> Verify Email -> Sign In -> (optional: Create Organization -> Set Active) -> Create Short URL -> ...\nFlow (development): Sign Up -> Sign In -> Create Short URL -> ...\n\nAuth uses Better Auth with the bearer plugin. The session token is returned in the `set-auth-token` header — not in the JSON body. Use `Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}` on protected routes.\n\nEmail verification is built into Better Auth at `GET /api/auth/verify-email?token=...`. In production, sign-in is blocked until verified.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000" },
    { "key": "sessionToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "verificationToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "jwtToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "shortCode", "value": "" },
    { "key": "organizationId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "orgSlug", "value": "acme" },
    { "key": "invitationId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "memberId", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["health"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Ready",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/ready", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["ready"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Auth OK",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('status ok', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('ok'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/ok",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "ok"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign Up (email)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const token = pm.response.headers.get('set-auth-token');",
                  "if (token) pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionToken', token);",
                  "pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-up/email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-up", "email"]
            },
            "description": "Creates an account. The session token is in the `set-auth-token` response header (bearer plugin).\n\nA personal organization is created automatically for the new user. In production, a verification email is sent and sign-in is blocked until verified."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Send Verification Email",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/send-verification-email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "send-verification-email"]
            },
            "description": "Resends the verification email. Use the same email as Sign Up.\n\nIn dev, the link is logged in the server console. In production, check your inbox or the Resend dashboard."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Email",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201, 302]));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-email?token={{verificationToken}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "verify-email"],
              "query": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{verificationToken}}" }]
            },
            "description": "Better Auth built-in route. Copy the `token` query param from the verification email link into the `verificationToken` collection variable, then run this (or click the link). Then run Sign In."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign In (email)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const token = pm.response.headers.get('set-auth-token');",
                  "if (token) pm.collectionVariables.set('sessionToken', token);",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-in/email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-in", "email"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "const orgId = res && res.session && res.session.activeOrganizationId;",
                  "if (orgId) pm.collectionVariables.set('organizationId', orgId);",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/get-session",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "get-session"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the current user + session. The session includes `activeOrganizationId` (the active tenant), captured here into the `organizationId` variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get JWT Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('jwtToken', res.token);",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/token",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a verifiable EdDSA JWT (jwt plugin). Validate statelessly via JWKS."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "JWKS",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/jwks",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "jwks"]
            },
            "description": "Public keys for verifying JWTs from GET /api/auth/token."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Request Password Reset",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"redirectTo\": \"{{baseUrl}}/reset-password\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/request-password-reset",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "request-password-reset"]
            },
            "description": "Sends a password reset email (logged in dev, sent via Resend in production)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign Out",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/sign-out",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "sign-out"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke All Sessions",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/revoke-sessions",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "revoke-sessions"]
            },
            "description": "Signs out everywhere — invalidates all sessions for the user."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Organization",
      "description": "Multitenancy via the Better Auth organization plugin, mounted under /api/auth/organization/*. All routes require `Authorization: Bearer {{sessionToken}}`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Check Slug",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"slug\": \"{{orgSlug}}\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/check-slug",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "check-slug"]
            },
            "description": "Checks whether an organization slug is available."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Organization",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "const id = res && (res.id || (res.organization && res.organization.id));",
                  "if (id) pm.collectionVariables.set('organizationId', id);",
                  "pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Acme Inc\",\n  \"slug\": \"{{orgSlug}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/create",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "create"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new organization with the caller as owner. Optional: `logo`, `metadata` (object), `keepCurrentActiveOrganization` (boolean). The new org id is captured into `organizationId`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Organizations",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/list",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "list"]
            },
            "description": "Lists organizations the current user belongs to."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Set Active Organization",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "const id = res && (res.id || (res.organization && res.organization.id));",
                  "if (id) pm.collectionVariables.set('organizationId', id);",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"organizationId\": \"{{organizationId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/set-active",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "set-active"]
            },
            "description": "Switches the active tenant for the current session. Pass `organizationId` or `organizationSlug`. Pass `organizationId: null` to clear it. After this, /api/urls operations act within this org."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Full Organization (active)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/get-full-organization",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "get-full-organization"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the active organization with members and invitations. Optionally pass `?organizationId=` or `?organizationSlug=` to target a specific org."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Organization",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": ["pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"organizationId\": \"{{organizationId}}\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"name\": \"Acme International\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/update",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "update"]
            },
            "description": "Updates org fields. `data` may include `name`, `slug`, `logo`, `metadata`. Requires admin/owner role."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Invite Member",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res && res.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('invitationId', res.id);",
                  "pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"teammate@example.com\",\n  \"role\": \"member\",\n  \"organizationId\": \"{{organizationId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/invite-member",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "invite-member"]
            },
            "description": "Invites a user by email (role: owner | admin | member). Sends the invitation email (logged in dev). The invitation id is captured into `invitationId`. Pass `resend: true` to re-send a pending invite."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Invitations",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/list-invitations?organizationId={{organizationId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "list-invitations"],
              "query": [{ "key": "organizationId", "value": "{{organizationId}}" }]
            },
            "description": "Lists invitations for the organization."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Invitation",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/get-invitation?id={{invitationId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "get-invitation"],
              "query": [{ "key": "id", "value": "{{invitationId}}" }]
            },
            "description": "Fetches a single invitation by id (used by the accept-invitation page)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Accept Invitation",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": ["pm.test('2xx success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]));"] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"invitationId\": \"{{invitationId}}\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/accept-invitation",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "accept-invitation"]
            },
            "description": "Accepts a pending invitation. Must be called while signed in as the invited user (the email must match)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reject Invitation",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"invitationId\": \"{{invitationId}}\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/reject-invitation",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "reject-invitation"]
            },
            "description": "Rejects a pending invitation (called by the invited user)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cancel Invitation",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{sessionToken}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"invitationId\": \"{{invitationId}}\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/organization/cancel-invitation",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "organization", "cancel-invitation"]
            },
            "description": "Cancels a pending invitation (called by an admin/owner of the org)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Members",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "const members = (res && (res.members || res.data)) || [];",
                  "if (members.length && members[0].id) pm.collectionVariables.set('memberId', members[0].id);",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
